### 5. Functional Breakdown (Application Pages)

This defines the 6 core pages of the **SAP Build Apps** application.

#### 1. Lead Management Page
* **Purpose:** Capture, qualify, and assign all new business leads.
* **Key Features:**
    * Customizable table (Company, Contact, Source, **LeadScore**, Status, etc.).
    * Auto-population of new leads found by the **Databricks** scraping engine.
    * Auto-sync from email inboxes (e.g., Gmail) and embedded web forms.
    * AI automatically drafts personalized reply suggestions.
    * **SAP Build Process Automation** triggers to auto-assign leads based on region or product interest.
    * One-click "Convert to Account" button.

#### 2. Contacts Management Page
* **Purpose:** Manage 360° profiles for all qualified people (clients, partners).
* **Key Features:**
    * Detailed profile with communication history, relationship tags (Distributor, Salon, Influencer), and purchase history.
    * Email sync to view and reply to emails directly within the CRM.
    * AI-generated "Contact Insights" summary (e.g., "Prefers WhatsApp; interested in Vitamin C line").
    * **Databricks** sentiment model identifies the tone of email replies ("Positive," "At Risk").

#### 3. Accounts Management Page
* **Purpose:** Organize client companies, retail chains, and distributors at the business level.
* **Key Features:**
    * Hierarchical view (e.g., Company -> Branches -> Contacts).
    * **SAP S/4HANA Integration:** Syncs and displays real-time sales data, billing history, and order status for each account.
    * **AI Account Health Score** (based on order frequency, payment history, and engagement).
    * A dedicated collaboration thread (like Lark or Teams) for each high-value account, integrated via **SAP Work Zone**.

#### 4. Activities Page
* **Purpose:** A smart calendar and unified log for all team tasks and touchpoints.
* **Key Features:**
    * Unified log of all calls, emails, meetings, and demos.
    * AI auto-logs activities from synced Gmail and calendars.
    * Natural language scheduling (e.g., "Book follow-up with GlowBar KL next Tuesday").
    * Automated reminders triggered by **SAP Build Process Automation**.

#### 5. Deals Page
* **Purpose:** Visually manage the sales pipeline from negotiation to closure.
* **Key Features:**
    * Kanban board view with drag-and-drop stages (Prospecting, Quoted, Negotiation, Closed Won).
    * **SAP S/4HANA Integration:** Syncs real-time product pricing and stock levels.
    * **AI Win Probability Score** for each deal, calculated by Databricks.
    * Built-in "Discount Approval Form" that triggers an **SAP Build Process Automation** workflow to the manager (Alex).
    * Manager receives approval request instantly in **SAP Work Zone**.

#### 6. Dashboard (Analytics)
* **Purpose:** Management overview of performance, trends, and geography, powered by **SAP Analytics Cloud**.
* **Key Features:**
    * Real-time KPI tiles (Total Leads, Conversion Rate, Top Product Trend, Top Rep).
    * **Intelligent Map:** An interactive map showing new leads by region, hot products trending per city, and sales pipeline heatmaps.
    * **Predictive Forecasting** (from Databricks model) for next-month revenue by product.
    * AI-generated summary box (e.g., "Sales up 14% in KL due to #SPF50 trend").

